    "This leads to a modified expression for the loop impedance that includes the IBR-induced voltage component, as shown in (2):Z loop = V loop + V comp (d) I loop,(2)where V comp (d) represents the voltage drop introduced by the IBR current flowing through the segment between the IBR and the fault.",
